To install menu generator into /usr/local, just type 'sudo make install'.
Edit 'prefix' in Makefile to install elsewhere.

Add a line something like:
 <menu id="pipe" label="Applications" icon="/usr/share/icons/gnome/24x24/status/folder-open.png" execute="obpipec"/>
to your ~/.config/openbox/menu.xml and restart openbox.

To include another desktop directory to read use ...execute="obpipec -d <DIR>"/>
To try reading .gtkrc-2.0 for the icon theme use ...execute="obpipec -i"/>

Changes

0.1 -  14 Apr 13
	first release - basics only

0.2 -  24 Apr 13 
	use the -d and -i switches
	try to look up icons from gtkrc-2.0
	handle unity desktop entries properly
